  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6593.49 sitting between the max negative gamma at 6590 (-12.9B) and max positive gamma at 6605 (+14.4B), dealers are in active hedging mode—buying weakness into 6590 and selling strength into 6605, creating a volatile 15-point compression zone. The breakout regime with -21.9B total GEX means any break below 6590 support will trigger aggressive dealer buying that amplifies the move lower, while a push above 6605 resistance forces dealer selling into strength. Watch 6590 as the critical fulcrum—hold it and we chop violently in this narrow range, lose it and expect accelerated selling pressure toward the 6580 wall.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect whippy action between 6590-6605 with violent moves if either level breaks.",
